# SocialAI — Cursor / Codex Project Rules

## Stack
- Frontend: React 18, Vite, React Router v6
- Backend: Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Realtime + Edge Functions)
- Styling: CSS modules + custom CSS variables (no Tailwind)
- AI: Grok API for generation, optimization, and quality scoring
- State: React Query (TanStack) for server state, React Context for auth/theme

## File Structure
src/
  admin/           — Admin workspace (routes, pages, components, styles)
  components/      — Shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, StatusBadge, PlatformIcon)
  Context/         — React contexts (AuthContext, ThemeContext, LogoutContext)
  hooks/           — Custom hooks (useLogout, useRealtimeKPIs, etc.)
  pages/           — User workspace pages
  router/          — Router config (router.jsx)
  services/        — Supabase client, authService, queryClient, mockService
  styles/          — Global CSS (theme.css, variables.css, design-system.css)
  utils/           — Auth routing, protectedRoute, helpers
supabase/
  functions/       — Edge functions (Deno)
  migrations/      — SQL migrations

## Critical Rules — Do Not Break These
1. posts is the canonical publishing lifecycle table
2. generations is the canonical AI creation table
3. Completed generations trigger a draft post creation via DB trigger — do not remove this trigger
4. Admin visibility uses RLS policies — never bypass auth.uid() checks
5. Lifecycle statuses must stay aligned with src/constants/statuses.js
6. audit_logs rows are IMMUTABLE — never UPDATE or DELETE them
7. content_versions with is_original: true are never overwritten
8. Admin routes are /app/admin/* only — never reuse user route paths
9. theme.css is the root theme source — only [data-theme] selectors, no .dark or html.dark
10. All destructive admin actions must write an audit_log entry

## Theme System
- ThemeContext sets data-theme="light" or data-theme="dark" on <html>
- CSS uses [data-theme="dark"] and [data-theme="light"] selectors only
- Do NOT use .dark, html.dark, or @media (prefers-color-scheme) for app theming
- Token namespace: --bg-*, --text-*, --accent, --border, --shadow-*

## Admin Role Logic
- super_admin: access to all /app/admin/* routes and all data
- org_admin: access to /app/admin/* routes, scoped to own organization only
- user: access to /app/dashboard, /app/generate, /app/calendar, /app/library, /app/settings only
- No role can access routes outside their scope — ProtectedRoute enforces this

## Data Patterns
- Never use window.alert(), window.confirm(), or window.prompt() anywhere
- All user-facing confirmations use in-app modal components
- Realtime updates patch individual records in React Query cache — never trigger full list refetch
- Every admin action that mutates data must show a visible success/error state

## Edge Functions
- Location: supabase/functions/
- Runtime: Deno
- Every function validates admin JWT and checks role scope before executing
- Every function writes to audit_logs on completion
- Never hard-delete user data from client code — use soft delete + approval workflow

## Component Conventions
- Shared primitives: QualityScoreBadge, ActivityStatusBadge, StatusBadge, PlatformIcon
- Use these instead of creating per-page status pill variations
- Admin shell layout: AdminLayout > AdminNavbar (fixed) + AdminSidebar (fixed) + .admin-content (scrollable)
- No component should define generic .card or .btn-primary — use shared design system classes
